             Data Scientist, Analytics
             IHS Markit Advanced Analytics – Washignton, DC
            IHS Markit is a company that has helped businesses and countries make better decisions with information and insight for over 50 years. Our core focus is on capital intensive industries (Automotive, Energy, Chemicals, Technology, Aerospace & Defense, Maritime, etc.) with a combined annual spend of more than $32 Trillion. Critically, these industries have highly interconnected supply chains and IHS – with deep expertise and unique data assets within each of the industries – is uniquely positioned to understand these connections and their impacts, both within and across industries, unlike any other company. Our vision, and next evolution as a company, is the convergence of our insights across the industries.
           The IHS Markit Advanced Analytics group has been challenged to fundamentally change the way we use data and subject matter expertise to answer key industry questions. To realize this vision, we are expanding our industry leading group with experts possessing the skills to turn data into commercial products and solutions. The IHS Markit Advanced Analytics group is looking for smart, driven, and creative individuals to help in the development of products, and lead our efforts by managing global teams of data scientists, and consultants in the development and delivery of novel analytic solutions for clients around the world. We have unparalleled information about every car on the road, every vessel in the ocean, and every oil well in the field – join us in leveraging our macroeconomic, industry, trade, price, and risk forecasts as we stand on the shoulders of our industry experts and change the way decisions are made. When our capabilities are brought together we have the opportunity to do what no one else can.
           Our colleagues at IHS Markit are passionate about the work we’re doing – we have a few ways in which you can help us do that work
            even better
           …
            Help us drive analysis:
            Apply your machine learning and advanced analytics skills (agent based modeling, random forest, support vector machines, neural networks, survival analysis, Bayesian statistics, etc.) to IHS Markit’s unique, industry leading data to surface new insights and develop new products.
            Be part of a unique team working across business lines with cutting edge analytics and technology to provide actionable results, support new and existing products and platforms, and to influence business decisions
            Grow your knowledge of the latest  data and analytical methodologies and technologies – Redshift, EC2, machine learning and more
            Cooperatively work across the analytics team to share knowledge and educate one another
           In order to make that happen, we’re looking for you to have these skills:
            Minimum education requirement of four year degree in statistics, computer science, mathematics, economics, or a similarly quantitative discipline. Additional education is preferred.
            Five (5) or more years of relevant advanced analytics experience – strong proficiency in advanced statistical, predictive and machine learning techniques (agent based modeling, random forest, support vector machines, neural networks, survival analysis, Bayesian statistics, etc).
            Demonstrated creative problem solving & critical reasoning abilities.
            Ability to understand business context and translate to develop appropriate analytics solutions
            Established ability to communicate effectively and proactively.
            Strong proficiency in R required.
            Experience writing code and using data science tools such as SQL, Python, Tableau, ArcGIS, and/or Hadoop highly desirable.
            Primary Location:
           Washington, DC
